'tee' command
-------------------
purpose	 redirecting also viewing through terminal
syntax	 cmd | tee filename
example	 date | tee out.txt

'chage' command
-------------------
purpose:	to define password aging policies
arguments:	-m, -M,-W.
example:	sudo chage -m 20 -M 60 -W 14 user_name

'useradd' command
-------------------
purpose:	to create a new user.
argumet:	-m (to map the default home directory with the user.
example:	sudo useradd -m user_name

'userdel'command
-------------------
purpose:	to delete a user account.
argument:	-r (without -r only the user entries will delete not the configurations and home dir)
example:	sudo userdel -r user_name.

'passwd' command
-------------------
purpose:	to set a password for the user account.
argument:	-l , -u.
example:	sudo passwd user_name		(set up the passwd)
		sudo passwd -l user_name	(lock the passwd)
		sudo passwd -u user_name	(unlock the passwd)

'groupadd' command
-------------------
purpose:	to create a group.
example:	sudo groupadd group_name

'groupdel' command
-------------------
purpose:	to delete a group.
example:	sudo groupdel group_name.

'usermod' command
-------------------
purpose:	to edit user,group functions,utilities etc.
arguments:	-a.
example:	sudo usermod -aG group_name user_name (without -a only the last added group will persist).

